<item>
            <title>[LU-19968] reduce testing for patches only affecting documentation</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19968</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=colmstea&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;colmstea&quot;&gt;colmstea&lt;/a&gt;, could you look why patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/64508&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/64508&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19736&quot; title=&quot;Add man page for llapi_get_obd_count()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19736&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-19736&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; man: Add man page for llapi_get_obd_count&quot;) did not trigger the auto{{-trivial}} functionality in Autotest?  The patch isn&apos;t modifying any code files, only man pages and the &lt;tt&gt;Makefile.am&lt;/tt&gt; under &lt;tt&gt;Documentation/&lt;/tt&gt; so that should be pretty safe (TBH building the patch would be enough, and running any testing adds no value).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, this patch ran a full test session, about 180h these days when the &lt;tt&gt;optional&lt;/tt&gt; sessions are included, which is overkill.  That is especially true when I saw hundreds of other test sessions running today...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="96413">LU-19968</key>
            <summary>reduce testing for patches only affecting documentation</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11310&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
