                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="493529" author="adilger" created="Tue, 21 Apr 2026 21:51:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nice!&#160; I can see my life getting better already, as I push new &lt;tt&gt;Documentation/man4&lt;/tt&gt; patches into Gerrit.&#160; Now I just need to make sure I don&apos;t poison those patches with some trivial change elsewhere in the tree (though thankfully &lt;tt&gt;contrib/&lt;/tt&gt; is also in the same boat).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="493522" author="colmstea" created="Tue, 21 Apr 2026 17:01:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a non-staged example of testing being skipped for a pure Documentation change: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63118&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63118&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="493455" author="colmstea" created="Mon, 20 Apr 2026 14:46:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This change was deployed on 4/18. I pushed a patch to test and it was marked +1 by Maloo as expected&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65427&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65427&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I created &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20170&quot; title=&quot;ATM: Use changed.py from master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-20170&quot;&gt;LU-20170&lt;/a&gt; for AT to pull the changed.py version from the tip of master rather than from the AT repo.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="493452" author="gerrit" created="Mon, 20 Apr 2026 13:23:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Charlie Olmstead &amp;lt;charlie@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65427&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/65427&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19968&quot; title=&quot;reduce testing for patches only affecting documentation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19968&quot;&gt;LU-19968&lt;/a&gt; - ATM: reduce testing for patches only affecting documentation&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: ed8674eb5b1b0ec1481d98000ad6e973a9c1183a&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="492293" author="colmstea" created="Wed, 1 Apr 2026 23:23:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Updated changed.py script in &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60584&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60584&lt;/a&gt; to skip testing for patches that only modify/add/delete given paths.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="491791" author="adilger" created="Tue, 24 Mar 2026 21:00:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think force-trivial would be the very most that should be done, but if it is clear that a patch is only affecting, say &lt;tt&gt;Documentation/&amp;#42;&lt;/tt&gt;,  &lt;tt&gt;LICENSES&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;lustre/ChangeLog&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;contrib/&lt;/tt&gt; then it doesn&apos;t really need any testing since those files don&apos;t affect any testable functionality.  A build would still be useful to verify that it doesn&apos;t break the packaging (e.g. extra files installed that are not packaged).  If we wanted to do &lt;b&gt;some&lt;/b&gt; testing, then a single x86 session with &lt;tt&gt;runtests&lt;/tt&gt; would be enough to at least verify the packages could be installed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Having a &quot;&lt;tt&gt;review-smoke&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; session that only ran &lt;tt&gt;runtests&lt;/tt&gt; takes about 5 minutes (excluding node-provisioning and lustre-initialization) and would be a good &quot;first session&quot; for every patch that gates whether the rest of the sessions should be scheduled, if there is high load on the test system.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="491781" author="colmstea" created="Tue, 24 Mar 2026 16:57:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There isn&apos;t any logic to force trivial/skip testing for documentation only changes. It should be easy to add. Would you like testing to be skipped and a +1 to be sent? Force trivial? Does this apply to all files under Documentation?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
